---
import { type Lang } from "@/i18n"

type Props = { lang: Lang }
const { lang } = Astro.props
---

<prose-content>
  {lang === "zh" ? (
    <>
      <h1>工艺说明</h1>

      <h2>技术栈</h2>
      <p>
        本站以 <a href="https://astro.build" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a>（静态站点生成）构建，部署于
        <a href="https://pages.github.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Pages</a>，无服务端运行时。
      </p>

      <h2>排版</h2>
      <p>
        正文衬线字体：<a href="https://fonts.google.com/noto/specimen/Noto+Serif+SC" rel="noopener noreferrer">Noto Serif SC</a>（中文），配合
        <a href="https://www.ibm.com/plex/" rel="noopener noreferrer">IBM Plex Sans</a>（西文界面字体）与
        IBM Plex Mono（行内代码与代码块）。字号采用流体排版比例尺（Utopia，min 16 px → max 18 px），以
        <code>clamp()</code> 连续缩放。
      </p>

      <h2>内容处理</h2>
      <p>
        Markdown 由 <a href="https://github.com/satterijun/astro-markdown-satteri" rel="noopener noreferrer">@astrojs/markdown-satteri</a> 处理；
        代码块渲染使用 <a href="https://expressive-code.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Expressive Code</a>
        （含可折叠区块与行号插件）；数学公式以
        <a href="https://temml.org" rel="noopener noreferrer">Temml</a> 直接编译为 MathML，无需 KaTeX 运行时。
      </p>

      <h2>配色</h2>
      <p>
        浅色主题采用「年鉴旧纸」调色板——以 OKLCH 色彩空间调制的暖米色底、茶褐色字、赤陶强调色，
        深色模式则为温暖黑底配浅中性灰。两种模式均已通过 WCAG AAA 对比度验证（正文 ≥ 7:1）。
        配色变量统一用 <code>light-dark()</code> 函数管理，随系统偏好或手动切换自动响应。
      </p>

      <h2>分发与发现</h2>
      <p>
        提供全文 <a href="/zh/rss.xml">RSS feed</a>，集成
        <a href="https://www.sitemaps.org" rel="noopener noreferrer">XML Sitemap</a>，
        无 cookie banner，无第三方追踪脚本，无广告。
        本站倾向 <a href="https://indieweb.org" rel="noopener noreferrer">IndieWeb</a> 理念：先发布于自己的域，再决定是否分发至他处。
      </p>

      <h2>立场</h2>
      <p>
        这是一块拒绝算法分发的数字领地。文章不追热点，不为平台优化。
        如果你能在这里读到一篇文章，是因为你主动找来——或有人把链接递给了你。
      </p>
    </>
  ) : (
    <>
      <h1>Colophon</h1>

      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <p>
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a> (static-site
        generation) and deployed to <a href="https://pages.github.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Pages</a> — no server runtime.
      </p>

      <h2>Typography</h2>
      <p>
        Serif body type: <a href="https://fonts.google.com/noto/specimen/Noto+Serif+SC" rel="noopener noreferrer">Noto Serif SC</a> (CJK), paired with
        <a href="https://www.ibm.com/plex/" rel="noopener noreferrer">IBM Plex Sans</a> (Latin UI) and
        IBM Plex Mono (inline code and code blocks). Font sizes follow a fluid type scale (Utopia,
        16 px → 18 px) and scale continuously via <code>clamp()</code>.
      </p>

      <h2>Content processing</h2>
      <p>
        Markdown is handled by <a href="https://github.com/satterijun/astro-markdown-satteri" rel="noopener noreferrer">@astrojs/markdown-satteri</a>.
        Code blocks are rendered with <a href="https://expressive-code.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Expressive Code</a>
        (collapsible sections and line-number plugins). Math equations compile directly to MathML
        via <a href="https://temml.org" rel="noopener noreferrer">Temml</a> — no KaTeX runtime needed.
      </p>

      <h2>Color</h2>
      <p>
        The light theme uses a "yearbook old-paper" palette — OKLCH-tuned warm parchment background,
        brown-ink body text, and terracotta accent. Dark mode flips to a warm black with light
        neutral grays. Both modes pass WCAG AAA contrast (≥ 7:1 for body text). Color tokens are
        managed with the <code>light-dark()</code> function and respond automatically to system
        preference or the manual toggle.
      </p>

      <h2>Distribution and discovery</h2>
      <p>
        Full-content <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a>, XML Sitemap included. No cookie banners,
        no third-party tracking scripts, no ads. This site leans toward
        <a href="https://indieweb.org" rel="noopener noreferrer">IndieWeb</a> principles: publish
        on your own domain first, then decide whether to syndicate elsewhere.
      </p>

      <h2>Stance</h2>
      <p>
        This is a piece of digital territory that refuses algorithmic distribution. Posts are not
        written to chase trends or optimize for platforms. If you're reading this, it's because
        you came looking — or someone handed you the link.
      </p>
    </>
  )}
</prose-content>
